[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    553[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [AWS Machine Learning Blog](https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/machine-learning/): Search for "time series" or "forecasting" for end-to-end implementation deep dives
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    554[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    555[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Open-Source Forecasting Libraries:**
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    556[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [Prophet (Meta)](https://facebook.github.io/prophet/): Classical decomposition method with sane defaults; in maintenance mode but still widely used
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    557[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [statsmodels](https://www.statsmodels.org/): The reference Python implementation for SARIMA, ETS, and most classical methods
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    558[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [Darts](https://unit8co.github.io/darts/): Modern Python forecasting library with a unified API across classical and deep learning methods
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    559[0m:[38;5;10m[49m - [GluonTS](https://ts.gluon.ai/): Probabilistic time series modeling toolkit; powers many of the deep learning methods in production cloud forecasting services
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    560[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    561[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ---
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    562[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    563[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## Estimated Implementation Time
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    564[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
